## SOL Ultra subagent budget

When the root agent uses `gpt-5.6-sol` with `ultra` reasoning:

- Spawn each child with `model="gpt-5.6-terra"`,
  `reasoning_effort="high"`, `service_tier="default"`, and
  `fork_turns="none"`.
- Give the child a self-contained task capsule containing its objective,
  relevant paths, constraints, required output, and verification criteria.
- Never silently inherit the root model, reasoning effort, service tier, or
  full conversation history.
- Run at most three child agents concurrently and spawn at most four distinct
  children in one user turn, including replacements.
- Do not allow child agents to spawn further agents.
- Reuse an existing child for closely related follow-up work when practical.
- If Terra High is unavailable or its result fails the stated verification
  criteria, explain the specific deficiency and proposed replacement model,
  reasoning effort, and service tier. Wait for explicit user approval before
  spawning the replacement. Use structured choices when available; otherwise
  ask a short plain-text confirmation.
- Never spawn a SOL Ultra child unless the user explicitly approves that exact
  escalation.
